body
    .body-wrapper#bubbleWrapper
        .bubbles#bubbleContainer
            script.
                var bubbles = document.getElementById('bubbleContainer');
                //- bubbles.setAttribute('data-0', 'top:1px;')
                //- bubbles.setAttribute('data-' + window.innerHeight, 'top:-' + window.innerHeight + 'px;');
                bubbles.setAttribute('data-0', 'opacity:1;')
                bubbles.setAttribute('data-' + (window.innerHeight * 0.75), 'opacity:0;');
            canvas#bubbles

        .panel.cover
            .container
                .hero
                    h1 Hack the Anvil
                    h2 Learn together. Create together.
                    p March 6-8 • Purdue University • 36 Hours
                    .button-row
                        a(href="registration.html")#[button.btn.btn-pink Sign up]

        .divider-image#baseDividerImage.divider1(data-center="background-position: 0% 0%;" data-bottom-top="background-position: 0% -50%;" data-top-bottom="background-position: 0% 50%;")
            canvas.slants(data-align="left" data-top="white" data-bottom="white")

        .panel.bg-white
            .container
                .spawn-bubbles.bubbles-left(data-align="left")
                .content.right
                    h1 OUR MISSION
                    p Our team’s mission is to ignite a group of #[span.t-pink imaginative], #[span.t-blue ambitious], and #[span.t-yellow inspired] students at Purdue University. That’s why we are hosting the first-ever Hack the Anvil, a 36-hour, 400-Purdue-student hackathon where teams of Boilermakers craft hardware and software projects that solve important real-world problems. Hack the Anvil ties together the ever-growing hacker community at Purdue with top-tier companies to support the development of remarkable student projects and personal relationships.
        
        .divider-image.divider2(data-center="background-position: 0% 0%;" data-bottom-top="background-position: 0% -50%;" data-top-bottom="background-position: 0% 50%;")
            canvas.slants(data-align="right" data-top="white" data-bottom="white")

        .panel.bg-white
            .container
                .spawn-bubbles.bubbles-right(data-align="right")
                .content.left
                    h1 FAQ
                    h4 What if I've never programmed before?
                    p That's perfect! We're going to have specialized tracks set up throughout the event just for beginners. You'll get to work with experienced hackers and learn to make something awesome!
                    h4 What can I make?
                    p Web, desktop, mobile, hardware- it’s up to you to make whatever kind of project you want as long as it is software-related.
                    h4 What's the prizes?
                    p We'll let you know soon :)
                    h4 Who can come?
                    p Any Purdue student is welcome to come, just make sure to register online before March 1st. Join your friends and create a team of up to four people!
                    h4 Have more questions?
                    p Email us day or night at #[a.t-yellow(href="mailto:team@hacktheanvil.com") team@hacktheanvil.com]!
       
        .divider-image.divider3(data-center="background-position: 0% 0%;" data-bottom-top="background-position: 0% -50%;" data-top-bottom="background-position: 0% 50%;")
            canvas.slants(data-align="left" data-top="white" data-bottom="white")

        .panel.bg-white
            .container
                .spawn-bubbles.bubbles-left(data-align="left")
                .content.right.schedule
                    h1 Schedule
                    h4 Friday, March 6th
                    .entry
                        p.time 7:00 pm
                        p.info Sponsor check-in begins.
                    .entry
                        p.time 8:00 pm
                        p.info Hacker check-in begins.
                    .entry
                        p.time 9:00 pm
                        p.info Opening Ceremonies.
                    .entry
                        p.time 10:00 pm
                        p.info Hacking begins!
                    h4 Saturday, March 7th
